  "text": "Counselling patients with T1Hg bladder cancer on their treatment options (bladder-sparing intravesical therapy versus cystectomy) is an extensive and delicate process. Factoring in risk of recurrence and progression, patient age and medical comorbidities that predict life expectancy and quality of life is one of the most daunting clinical challenges facing urologists. [CITATION_1] Patients should be thoroughly informed about the risks of progression to muscle-invasive disease or development of metastases. Patients must be instructed that vigilant surveillance of symptoms is imperative when receiving conservative therapy.",
